article.headline: Montana State 68, Portland State 58
article.story:
PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Kati Burrows scored 22 points and grabbed
13 rebounds for a double-double Thursday as Montana State beat
Portland State 68-58 for the Bobcats' first Big Sky road victory of
the season.

Alyssa Nelson added 13 points while Briana Fields and Scotta
Morton added 10 each for Montana State (9-15, 3-8 Big Sky).

The Bobcats rallied from a 27-22 halftime deficit, shooting 52
percent from the field in the second half. MSU opened the final
stanza on a 10-5 run to tie the score at 32 points after a Nelson
three-pointer.

Portland State (2-21, 0-11) regained the lead before the Bobcats
went to 41-39 on a Nelson jumper with 12:28 remaining. PSU tied the
game at 43 on a Heidi Stuart basket with 9:35 left. MSU took a 9-2
run over the next two minutes for the victory.

Stuart led the Vikings with 18 points.
